Kaizer Chiefs defender Lorenzo Gordinho has admitted that the club are delighted to see the fans coming back to support the team following a recent five-match winning streak.After some difficult periods in 2016 during which coach Steve Komphela's future was called into question, the Glamour Boys have since risen to the top of the Premiership standings.As such, Gordinho believes the change in fortunes has contributed to the improved support. He told the club's official website, "It really feels good that our fans are coming back to the stadium and supporting us.&nbsp;"The confidence is there, they are happy with the team and believing in us again, and that gives us the boost we need on game day to get the positive result."The Amakhosi next face Ajax Cape Town in a league encounter at Athlone Stadium on Saturday. The action gets underway from 20:15 in the Mother City.